{{BLP sources|date=January 2011}}
'''Ronald Bon de Sousa Pernes''' ({{IPAc-en|d|ə|_|ˈ|s|uː|z|ə}}; born 1940 [[Switzerland]]) is a Canadian philosopher and academic.

==Biography==
De Sousa is an Emeritus Professor at the Department of Philosophy of the [[University of Toronto]], which he joined in 1966. He is best known for his work in [[philosophy of emotions]], and has also made contributions to [[philosophy of mind]] and [[philosophy of biology]]. He was elected a fellow of the [[Royal Society of Canada]] in 2005.<ref>[http://rsc-src.ca/en/search-fellows?keywords_44=&first_name=&last_name=&display_name=University%20of%20Toronto&election_year_21=&academy_25=All&division_24=All&discipline_23=All&is_deceased=0&sort_by=last_name&sort_order=ASC&page=6 RSC Fellows search]. [[Royal Society of Canada]]. Retrieved October 4, 2016.</ref>

De Sousa possesses both UK and Canadian citizenship. Educated in Switzerland and England, he took his B.A. at [[New College, Oxford|New College]], [[Oxford University]] in 1962, and his Ph.D. at [[Princeton University]] in 1966. He has contributed to and is frequently [http://plato.stanford.edu/search/searcher.py?query=Ronald+de+Sousa cited] in the ''[[Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy]]''.

